definitions.definition: To run a diff program on (files or items) so as to produce a description of the differences between them, as for a patch file .
To compare two files or other objects, manually or otherwise.
To win a fight against another, with a defined level of difficulty . Usually used when power scaling fictional characters.

main_definition: ( transitive , computing ) To run a diff program on (files or items) so as to produce a description of the differences between them, as for a patch file .
secondary_definitions: ( transitive , computing ) To compare two files or other objects, manually or otherwise.
( transitive , fandom slang ) To win a fight against another, with a defined level of difficulty . Usually used when power scaling fictional characters.
